sentences: Váša Příhoda (22 August 1900 – 26 July 1960) was a Czech violinist and minor composer.
His father, Alois Příhoda, was his first teacher and remained so for ten years.
Váša studied privately with Jan Mařák (a student of Otakar Ševčík), making his first public concert at age 13, playing the 4th Violin Concerto by Mozart.
Vienna was his base of operations for many years though he taught in Prague, Munich, and Salzburg as well.
He played recitals with pianist Alfred Holeček in the Rudolfinum Music Hall, and performed Dvořák's Violin Concerto in Smetana Hall of the Municipal House during the Prague Spring Festival.
